# How does angular interact with backends

In the angular app you generate data like posts or recipes or whatever you have in your application and you want to store that data in a database.

You also want to fetch it from there when the app restarts.

You don't connect angular to a database directly. 

You want to make sure your app is secure. There's an article about it.

More on Securing JavaScript in the Browser: https://academind.com/learn/javascript/hide-javascript-code/

Learn how to build a REST API: https://academind.com/learn/node-js/building-a-restful-api-with/